
[1]flippant

   FLIP'PANT, a. [L. labor, to slide or slip, and to liber, free.]

   1. Of smoother, fluent and rapid speech; speaking with ease and
   rapidity; having a voluble tongue; talkative.

   2. Pert; petulant; waggish.

   Away with flippant epilogues.
     __________________________________________________________________

